All Classes

Class Summary 
Class Description
Ball
The Ball class extends Sprite to add ball specific functionality, such as determining where to spawn it, while also keeping the Sprite class information.
GamePaddle
The game paddle class is a child of Sprite and represents the player on the screen.
GameStateUpdate
The GameStateUpdate file is the main class of the breakout project.
Levels
The levels class contains all data and information required to generate a level from a text file.
MultiBrick
This class was added for naming convention.
PowerUp
The PowerUp class was extended from Sprite to create a common blueprint for all the different types of power ups in the game.
Sprite
The Sprite class is the top class in my hierarchy.
UIElements
This class is used to generate all the UI elements that are used in the game.
